<!--
========================================================================================
PROJECT: Alternating Current (AC) Interactive Classroom - เครื่องมือเรียนรู้ไฟฟ้ากระแสสลับ
VERSION: 1.2.0 (Academic Math Board Edition)
AUTHOR/CREATOR: Gemini (Google Web Tier)
ACADEMIC ATTRIBUTION: Inspired by opensimlab.org

========================================================================================
DESCRIPTION / รายละเอียดโครงการ:
This interactive web application is designed as an educational tool for physics and electrical 
engineering classrooms. It bridges the gap between theoretical calculations and real-time visual 
dynamics of alternating current (AC) through a purely resistive circuit load. 

แอปพลิเคชันเว็บเชิงโต้ตอบนี้ได้รับการออกแบบขึ้นเพื่อเป็นเครื่องมือช่วยสอนในห้องเรียนฟิสิกส์และวิศวกรรมไฟฟ้า 
โดยเชื่อมโยงทฤษฎีทางคณิตศาสตร์เข้ากับการแสดงผลของรูปคลื่นไฟฟ้ากระแสสลับ (AC) บนโหลดความต้านทานบริสุทธิ์แบบเรียลไทม์

========================================================================================
KEY FUNCTIONALITIES / ฟังก์ชันเด่น:
1. Theory & Principles: Detailed dual-language documentation explaining AC basics, Sine waves, 
   and Root Mean Square (RMS) equations.
2. Interactive Waveform Simulator: High-fidelity interactive oscilloscope powered by D3.js, 
   rendering voltage (V) and current (I) curves dynamically with real-time parameter tweaking.
3. Step-by-Step Mathematical Board: Interactive worksheets calculating values in both forward 
   (Peak to RMS) and reverse (RMS to Peak with Ohm's verification) directions. Supports:
   - Sync Mode: Pulls values directly from the interactive simulator.
   - Manual Board / Randomization Mode: Decouples calculations to allow teachers or students to 
     input custom exam values or auto-generate randomized academic problems.

========================================================================================
ARCHITECTURE & DESIGN TOKENS / สถาปัตยกรรมและการออกแบบ:
- Tech Stack: Pure HTML5, Tailwind CSS (Tailwind CDN v3), D3.js (Data Visualization v7), Vanilla JS.
- Responsive Design: Implements fluid grid structures and SVG coordinate scaling via HTML5 ResizeObserver, 
  eliminating the risk of canvas clipping on mobile devices.
- UI Aesthetics: Light and dark contrast typography, smooth transition animations, and custom range inputs.
- Localization (i18n): Uses a localized JSON dictionary mapping TH/EN keys on 'data-i18n' attributes.
- Math Formatting: Rendered using structured HTML fraction structures styled with CSS to produce elegant, 
  textbook-grade mathematical expressions.

========================================================================================
DEVELOPER EXTENSION PATHWAYS / คู่มือการพัฒนาต่อยอด (สำหรับวิศวกรผู้พัฒนาต่อในอนาคต):
This application is designed to be highly modular and easily extendable for advanced electronics curricula:
- Reactance & Impedance (R-L-C Circuits): To add Inductive (L) or Capacitive (C) reactive elements:
  1. Introduce Phase Angle Shift (phi / φ) into the sine functions: v(t) = Vp * sin(wt), i(t) = Ip * sin(wt - phi).
  2. Update the Impedance (Z) calculation: Z = sqrt(R^2 + (XL - XC)^2) instead of purely R.
  3. Draw a phasor diagram SVG showing the phase difference vector.
- Power Calculations:
  - Add Active Power (P = Vrms * Irms * cos(phi)), Reactive Power (Q), and Apparent Power (S) calculations.
========================================================================================
-->
