                        <p class="text-slate-700 text-sm mb-3" data-i18n="rmsDesc">
                            Because AC changes constantly, we use RMS to define an "effective" steady value. 220V AC from a wall socket is actually 220V RMS, which delivers the same heating power as 220V DC.
